original: Lundberg, Gunnar Johanne^s, komminister, Hjälteby, f. 20/10/08 i Kungsbacka av kyrkoh. Viktor Lundberg o. Ebba Natt och Dag. G. 39 m. Gurli Torborg Börjesson. Barn: Mats f. 40, Bengt 41, Maj 46. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 28, teol. fil. ex. 30, teol. kand. o. prakt, teol. prov 33, prästex. o. prästv. 34. Pastorsadj. i Backa, Mölndal, Grime-ton, Tölö, v. pastor i Valida 38-39, kommin. i Valla fr. 39. Ordf. i kyr-kostänmna, kyrkoråd o. skolstyr., led. av barnav :nd.
translated:
Lundberg, Gunnar Johanne^s, curate, Hjälteby, born on 20/10/08 in Kungsbacka, son of pastor Viktor Lundberg and Ebba Natt och Dag. Married in 1939 to Gurli Torborg Börjesson. Children: Mats, born in 1940, Bengt in 1941, Maj in 1946. 

Education: Graduated from high school in Gothenburg in 1928, received a bachelor's degree in theology in 1930, completed practical theology exam and theological exam in 1933, and obtained a pastor's diploma and was ordained in 1934. 

Work experience: Assistant pastor in Backa, Mölndal, Grime-ton, Tölö, acting pastor in Valida from 1938-1939, and curate in Valla from 1939. 

Positions held: Chairman of the church finance committee, church council, and school board, member of the child welfare board.
